build/
vendor/
!src/pkg/vendor/
# webui.res is tracked — it's the binary output of fpcres webui.rc /
# brcc32 webui.rc and embeds webui.html into the gateway binary via the
# {$R webui.res} directive in PasClaw.Gateway.WebUI.pas. Committing it
# lets Delphi users + fresh clones run the gateway without first having
# fpcres / brcc32 on PATH. Editing webui.html requires also regenerating
# webui.res (the Makefile rule does this automatically on `make`; Delphi
# users run brcc32 webui.rc).
*.o
*.ppu
*.compiled
*.lps
*.bak
*.exe
*~
.DS_Store
